items.text:
We‚Äôre seeking talented local actors for an upcoming short film shooting mid-November in the Vancouver area.

Logline:

After her brother kills the nanny who tormented them as children, a teenage girl must cover up the crime while fractured memories of their past resurface ‚Äî forcing her to choose between protecting him or saving herself.

Production Details

 Location: Vancouver, BC

Shoot Dates: Mid-November (exact dates TBA)

 Genre: Psychological Drama / Thriller

 Non-Union / Paid

ROLES

Scarlett (16‚Äì18)

Levelheaded and fiercely protective, Scarlett has carried the burden of shielding her younger brother since childhood. Calm under pressure but weighed down by responsibility, she‚Äôll sacrifice everything to keep him safe.

Sawyer (14-15 years old)

Sensitive and unguarded, Sawyer is still haunted by the trauma of their childhood. Desperate to protect himself, he makes a choice that leads to violence and binds him to his sister‚Äôs protection.

Katherine (30s)

Outwardly polished and dependable, Katherine hides a cold, controlling nature. To the world she‚Äôs a caretaker ‚Äî but to the children, she‚Äôs a source of lasting fear and trauma.

Joan (White woman, 40s)

A sharp-eyed, restless neighbor, Joan masks her loneliness with judgment and suspicion. Always watching from the sidelines, her curiosity turns dangerous when she uncovers more than she was meant to see.

Younger Scarlett (10‚Äì12)

Mature beyond her years, Scarlett shoulders the unspoken role of protector. Cautious and observant, she looks out for her younger brother even when she longs to just be a child herself.

Younger Sawyer (8‚Äì10)

Sensitive and unguarded, Sawyer depends on his sister‚Äôs protection and struggles to make sense of the cruelty around him.

Adam (Dad, 30s‚Äì40s)

Well-meaning but distracted, Adam prioritizes work over family life, leaving his children vulnerable in his absence.

Addison (Mom, 30s‚Äì40s)

Career-focused and often absent, Addison means well but unintentionally leaves Scarlett with the burden of protecting her brother.

 To Submit:

Please send your headshot, resume, and demo reel (if available) to thethingsweburyshortfilm@gmail.com  with the subject line:

‚Äú[ROLE NAME] ‚Äì [Your Name]‚Äù

Once we‚Äôve received your email, we‚Äôll send out the audition slides and next steps.

Hi everyone! I'm Rue Dawson! I'm an actor and a temporary young filmmaker casting for my feature film 'All That We Feared'.

This is a Sci-fi psychological thriller passion project that I've been working on for some time now and I've had some last minute drop outs in the cast! 

LOCATION: Hatfield, Hertfordshire, England.
FILMING DATES: 22nd October, 2nd November, 3rd November.
PAYMENT: UNPAID! Travel and Accommodation is NOT covered. Food + Drink will be provided.

Roles Needed:

Main MALE role:
-16+
-Playing age 17-21
-Days Needed: All
-Any Ethnicity

-16+
-Playing age

-Ethnicity: White

Side FEMALE role:
-16+
-Playing age: ANY
-Days Needed: 2nd November
-Any Ethnicity

Deadline: ASAP But no later than the 14th October.

Social Media:

Rdawsonproductions@outlook.com

With ONLY 10 DAYS LEFT, make sure you‚Äôve got your tickets as the countdown has begun for our highly anticipated Actors and Filmmakers Networking Event on Sunday, October 26th! Are you ready to take a transformative step in your career? This is your moment!

 

For years, Marble Academy has proudly facilitated these events. Following the incredible turnout at our June gathering, which drew over 90 attendees, we hope to build on this success.

If you haven't experienced this event before, prepare for an unforgettable time. It's an incredible opportunity to connect with talented actors, visionary directors, influential producers, and skilled crew members who are eager to collaborate on your next project. For those who have attended in the past, you know that each gathering is not just productive but also a fantastic blend of familiar faces and new connections just waiting to be made.

 

We‚Äôre also thrilled to announce that the talented Lisa Barton from Lisa Barton photography will be joining us at the event to showcase her stunning work. If you‚Äôre in need of captivating headshots, looking to refresh your current images, or simply aiming to elevate your professional presence, this is the perfect moment to make it happen.

 

Mark your calendars for Sunday, October 26th, from 2 PM to 6:30 PM at HOME Mcr, located at 2 Tony Wilson Place, Manchester, M15 4FN.

MY MOMMA‚ÄôS ERA: THE MUSICAL ‚Äì SEEN THROUGH MY MOTHER‚ÄôS LENS

Saturday, November 8, 2025
Greenwood Oasis Theater ‚Äì 7621 S. Greenwood Ave, Chicago, IL
Showtime: 7 PM | VIP Experience: 4 PM | Doors Open: 6 PM
FREE PARKING

Come dressed in your best 40s, 50s, 60s, or 70s attire!
(It‚Äôs recommended ‚Äî not required ‚Äî for the full experience!)

Step back in time and experience a powerful musical journey through the Great Migration, Bronzeville‚Äôs rich Black history, and the soul of World War II-era Chicago ‚Äî told through acting, singing, dancing, and narration.

 Featuring unforgettable portrayals of:
Billie Holiday, Nat King Cole, Ella Fitzgerald, Dinah Washington, Cab Calloway, Etta James
Plus a moving tribute to Minnie Riperton, Chicago‚Äôs own.

A dynamic cast. Real stories. Legendary music.
This is more than entertainment ‚Äî it‚Äôs edutainment.

TICKETS & GROUP BENEFITS
Group rates (10+) already discounted online
Call 773-655-3575 for Senior & Youth group discounts!

Eventbrite (Use code: MyMommasEra2025):
 https://www.eventbrite.com/e/my-mommas-era-the-musical-stage-play-tickets-1302271441939?aff=oddtdtcreator

Zeffy (No fees to us!):
 https://www.zeffy.com/en-US/ticketing/my-mommas-era-the-musical-stage-play

 SUPPORT THE MOVEMENT ‚Äì DONATE TODAY
Dream Real Theatre Company is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit using the arts to educate, inspire, and transform.

Zeffy (tax-deductible):
https://www.zeffy.com/en-US/donation-form/donate-to-make-a-difference-19332

 PayPal:
https://www.paypal.com/donate?hosted_button_id=4HEYR2LBTP8J8

Zelle: 773-655-3575 

‚ÄúWe will not hide them from their children, but tell to the coming generation the glorious deeds of the Lord‚Ä¶‚Äù ‚Äì Psalm 78:4

Tag a friend, post your outfit inspo, and share the legacy!

PLAYBOX PRODUCTIONS ‚Äî NOW SEEKING FINAL CREW MEMBERS

**We‚Äôre bringing a few more people aboard an already full production team for George Orwell‚Äôs *****1984*****, directed by M.A.C.**

We‚Äôre looking for:
* **Assistant Producer**
* **Social Media / Marketing** Manager
* **Sound Board Operator**
* **Lighting Board Operator**

Performances run **December 4‚Äì7, 2025** at **Three Stories Theater (937 Liberty Ave, Downtown Pittsburgh)**.

Our **cast and crew of over 30 artists** are already deep in rehearsals and production work, and our design team has fully built out the world of the show. We‚Äôre looking for a few final team members to join the effort and help bring this ambitious production to completion.

**ASSISTANT PRODUCER**

Supports the Executive Producer with logistics, communications, scheduling, and coordination across departments. Ideal for someone organized, proactive, and interested in hands-on producing experience in a professional theatre environment.

**SOCIAL MEDIA / MARKETING MANAGER**

Join our marketing team to help manage social channels, coordinate content posting, and support our show rollout.
We already have **two resident photographers/videographers** and a **backlog of content ready to be edited, polished, and posted**. You‚Äôll be shaping how this production is presented to the public.

SOUND & LIGHTING BOARD OPERATORS

We have professional **sound and lighting designers** who have already built out the show‚Äôs systems and cues ‚Äî we‚Äôre simply looking for **two operators** to put that design work into action during **tech week and performances**.
Experience with QLab (for Sound) or ETC lighting consoles (for Lighting) is helpful, but a good sense of focus and teamwork is most important.

**COMPENSATION TYPE:** Volunteer / Possible post-show stipend
*(We want to be transparent: these are volunteer positions, but if funds allow, a small stipend may be available after the production.) *

**DATES & COMMITMENTS:**
* **Rehearsals (for reference):** Sundays, 6‚Äì9 PM starting August 3, 2025
Trust Arts Education Center ‚Äî 807 Liberty Ave, Pittsburgh, PA
* **Tech Week:** November 24 ‚Äì December 3, 2025 (dark day on Thanksgiving)
* **Performances:** December 4‚Äì7, 2025 (5 performances total)
Three Stories Theater ‚Äî 937 Liberty Ave, Pittsburgh, PA

We‚Äôre happy to work with your schedule ‚Äî please share any known conflicts when reaching out.

**TO APPLY**
Please email **playboxpgh@gmail.com** with:
* Resume (or a brief note on your experience and interest)
* Availability during tech week and performances

If it seems like a good fit, we‚Äôll be in touch right away!

Thank you,
Marc Palombo
**PLAYBOX PRODUCTIONS**

paid role 3 days @¬£350 day
very specific role to replace talent that is 6 months pregnant
playing age 25-30 female blonde hair size 10.
non speaking
15 min short film for outdoor clothing brand
you will need to:
drive a old (1972) landrover up a muddy track - it breaks down.
get out in a backless ball gown and heels and walk into the wood/footpath towards the village
end up with torn dress and no shoes walking in mud/undergrowth feeling that your being followed
find old ramblers hut in a panic/stress and get changed into brands gear that is hanging up in a dispaly cabinet by smashing open the glass front

run and hide in trees/get muddy paint face in combat style then fall into an abyss (greenscreen to crashmatt)
wake up in bed from the dream with the gown on the wardrobe, but the muddy clothes on the floor.
1 day in studio in Redruth, Cornwall 2 days on location probably near St Austell (waiting on permits) currently flexible shoot days scheduled between Nov 3rd and 9th.
will need 2 full length shots, 1 in a dress and 1 in fairly tight fitted gym gear or similar a full frontal face and a side/profile shot.
editor needs ot be able to match you to the current talent who has done other work for them

Client will be making descion on applications.

items.text: Hi everyone, I just wanted to introduce myself. I'm Madison, I am 18 and I live on the outskirts of Sheffield. I have always been in love with acting, modelling and performing, creating contrasting characters when going from project to project and this is always one of my favourite things to do! Saying this, I always believe in putting a little of your own personality into each role so you always are being you no matter what! I would be delighted if any roles come up for me or if anyone wants to direct message me through Facebook, I will be happy to share. Thank you for letting me share a little bit about myself and I will definitely do another post soon. Mwah! X

Have you ever wondered why some people simply fill the room the moment they walk in?
It‚Äôs not magic ‚Äî it‚Äôs presence. And it‚Äôs something you can actually train.

You‚Äôll learn how to connect more deeply with your body, attention, and authenticity ‚Äî whether you‚Äôre on stage, teaching, performing, or simply engaging with others in everyday life.

üé•** PAID CASTING CALL**

We are casting several roles for a series of short narrative pieces that highlight the stories of real families supported by our organization. These stories portray authenticity, warmth, and emotional depth.

**Location:** East Vancouver
**Audition Date:** October 20th

**Shooting Date:** October 23rd; must be available from 10-4 (you will not be needed the entire day)
**Compensation:** $200

**We are looking for actresses/actors to play: **

**Bruna**
* Female, late 20s to mid-40s
* Mother; caring and loving. Must convey determination, worry, and hope while navigating financial and emotional challenges for her children.

**Aisha**
* Female, early 30s to mid-40s

After the success of our last workshop we're running another at the end of this month.

Actors are you looking to earn good money between acting gigs that also keeps your skills sharp? Get paid to travel the word and even fly business class? This is all possible in the lucrative world of roleplay, where your transferable skills as an actor make you an incredibly valuable asset in the world of training and development.

Act One Roleplay has over forty years combined experience, working domestically and internationally, across a whole host of industries and law enforcement agencies such as the CIA and UK Counter Terrorism. Our team have facilitated workshops and roleplayed across five continents, playing a part in making positive change whilst earning a good living.

We will be running our three-hour workshop, Introduction to Roleplay; Witness and Suspect Interviewing on Saturday the 31st of October from 1-4pm at Theatre Deli, in central London priced at ¬£60.

The workshop is a starters guide to the world of roleplay and what it can offer you. In small groups, we cover the theoretical aspects of the work before putting it into practice. This is then followed by a Q&A session, meaning participants leave the session armed with an immersive experience and confident in starting their roleplay journey.

If you‚Äôre interested in taking part in this or any future workshops, please contact us info@actoneroleplay.com

items.text:
Halloüëãüèª Wir suchen f√ºr unser neues No- Budget- Serien- Projekt noch 4 hobbym√§√üige Schauspieler*innen (m/w/d), sowie eine Regieassistenz (m/w/d) und Drehorte f√ºr unser neues Projekt! 

Titel: Siegerlandchaos Staffel 2: Traumawut + Abschlussepisode: Untergangseuphorie 

Genre: Krimi mit Fantasy- Elementen, Drama 

Logline:
Der Fokus liegt auf Lea, welche lernen muss, mit ihrem Trauma umzugehen, und dabei sowohl eine zerst√∂rerische als auch vers√∂hnliche Seite an sich entdeckt. Au√üerdem stellen sich die Fragen, was in Zukunft aus Sherlock Wickels Detektei werden soll und wer ein echtes oder ein falsches Spiel spielt. 

Zusammenfassung
Ausgangspunkt: Bei einem tragischen Ereignis verliert Lea ihre Ehefrau Maja, sowie so ziemlich alles, was ihr etwas bedeutet. Es stellen sich die Fragen, ob Maja noch lebt oder nicht, und wo der Verantwortliche f√ºr das Drama steckt. Lea gelangt langsam aber sicher an ihr Limit, w√§hrend Sherlock Wickel sie im Stich zu lassen scheint. 

Konflikt: Es gibt mehrere Konflikte. Eine Psychiatrie sollte Ben Saalfeld heilen, aber verdarb ihn, Aufgrund der Umst√§nde. Rache m√∂chte er an Sherlock Wickel, Markus Wattson und insbesondere Lea nehmen. Hilfe bekommt er dabei von Sarahs Erzfeind Ludwig, beruhend auf Gegenseitigkeit. Ludwig m√∂chte mit Jacks Kette, Sarah und Maja einen moralisch zwiesp√§ltigen Plan umsetzen, um sich selbst von Auswirkungen seiner Schuld zu befreien. Gleichzeitig geht es innerhalb seiner Organisation ebenfalls nicht mit rechten Dingen zu. 

Aufl√∂sung: Am Ende erh√§lt Lea wichtige Erkenntnisse √ºber 's sich selbst Verzeihen. Die Organisation wird √ºberf√ºhrt und die Detektei geschlossen. Es gibt Vers√∂hnungen, Happy Ends und Drama. Maja, Emmas bzw. Jillians Eltern, Ludwig, Liora und Ben werden sterben. Sherlock Wickel und Lea lernen, das Gl√ºck in kleinen Momenten zu sehen. 

Stimmung: Intensiv, d√ºster, humorvoll, spannend, mysteri√∂s, actiongeladen, nah an realen Erfahrungen mit Traumata 

Besonders geeignet f√ºr Menschen, die sich tiefer mit Gef√ºhlen auseinandersetzen m√∂chten. 

Das Drehbuch enth√§lt 125 Seiten, wovon bereits 11 gedreht wurden. Gedreht wird vermutlich wie gewohnt in Plittershagen (Freudenberg, NRW, nahe Siegen) und einem noch unbekannten Drehort als Leas zu Hause. Es sind ggf. Hunde vor Ort, weshalb Tierliebhaber erw√ºnscht sind :)

Ziel des Projekts: Wir m√∂chten mit einer packenden Geschichte die Leute dazu bewegen, dar√ºber nachzudenken, wer sie denn eigentlich wirklich sind. Au√üerdem wollen wir beim Dreh mehr Erfahrung sammeln, uns Qualitativ im Vergleich zu Staffel 1 massivst steigern und die 'Jack'- Timeline meiner Geschichten beenden. 

Wenn alle einverstanden sind, w√ºrde ich nach M√∂glichkeit gerne im Winter mit dem Dreh weitermachen. Diesmal stehe ich auf jeden Fall, im Gegensatz zu bei Mafialiebe, komplett zu Story, Handlung und Co. Ich finde, diese Geschichte bietet einen bestm√∂glichen Abschluss f√ºr die Reihe 'Siegerlandchaos' und ich w√ºrde mich sehr freuen, wenn wir das dann zusammen und in besserer Qualit√§t hinkriegen üòä Da das Drehbuch auch um Einiges k√ºrzer und auf weniger Charakter- Konstellationen beschr√§nkt ist, gehe ich auch von einer schnelleren Umsetzungsm√∂glichkeit als bei Staffel 1: Mafialiebe aus. Drehtage w√ºrden diesmal nach M√∂glichkeit komplett danach ausgerichtet, wer an welchem Tag nach Absprache Zeit hat. 

Ver√∂ffentlicht soll die 2. Staffel mitsamt Bonusepisode ebenfalls auf YouTube werden. 

Gesuchte Rollen:

Ludwig Cifer - Spielalter 40-50 (m/d) - 1 Drehtag - Mafiaboss, intelligent, bedrohlich, ist sehr rassistisch, trans* und behindertenfeindlich, schuldbeladen, gerissen, stirbt am Ende 

Ben Saalfeld - Spielalter 17-18 (m/d) - 1 Drehtag - hasserf√ºllt, rachs√ºchtig, genie√üend, √§ngstlich, spielt Psychospielchen mit seinen Opfern, stark, stirbt am Ende, nachdem er wichtige Erkenntnisse erh√§lt 

Luna Drews - Spielalter 20-30 (w/d) - 1 Drehtag - freundlich, f√ºrsorglich, zuh√∂rend, lebensfroh, ernst, heimlich schwanger, blonde Haare 

Psychologin - Spielalter 20-60 - 1 Drehtag - zuh√∂rend, ernst

Bereits 8 Darsteller*innen sind Teil des Teams.

Zus√§tzlich suchen wir einen neuen Drehort f√ºr Leas und Majas zu Hause. 

Ich suche keine Leute, die sagen: Ja, mach ich mal mit. Ich suche Leute, die sagen: Ja, das w√§re voll cool, dabei zu sein! 

Wenn Interesse besteht, meldet euch gerne bei mir :)
jappycreations@gmail.com 

Zu mir: Ich bin Sarah Marie Sch√§fer, geb. am 01.10.2003 in Siegen, und wohne aktuell in der N√§he von Siegen in einem kleinen Dorf. Nach dem ich meinem verstorbenen Hund Jack versprach, meine Pl√§ne in die Tat umzusetzen und gl√ºcklich zu werden, tat ich dies mit dem Beginn meines ersten Serienprojekts, das abgeschlossen wurde. Fortan spielte ich auch Theater und schloss einige andere Pl√§ne ab. In der Schauspielerei habe ich meinen Weg gefunden und m√∂chte diesen weitergehen. Trotz vieler H√ºrden, wie Autismus, Transidentit√§t und einigen gesundheitlichen Problemen gebe ich nicht so schnell auf und bleibe an meinen Pl√§nen dran.

Anbei sind ein paar Szenen aus Staffel 1 Folge 8 als Vorgeschmack :)

Halloüëãüèª Wir suchen f√ºr unser neues No- Budget- Serien- Projekt noch 4 hobbym√§√üige Schauspieler*innen (m/w/d), sowie eine Regieassistenz (m/w/d) und Drehorte f√ºr unser neues Projekt! 

Titel: Siegerlandchaos Staffel 2: Traumawut + Abschlussepisode: Untergangseuphorie 

Genre: Krimi mit Fantasy- Elementen, Drama 

Logline:
Der Fokus liegt auf Lea, welche lernen muss, mit ihrem Trauma umzugehen, und dabei sowohl eine zerst√∂rerische als auch vers√∂hnliche Seite an sich entdeckt. Au√üerdem stellen sich die Fragen, was in Zukunft aus Sherlock Wickels Detektei werden soll und wer ein echtes oder ein falsches Spiel spielt. 

Zusammenfassung
Ausgangspunkt: Bei einem tragischen Ereignis verliert Lea ihre Ehefrau Maja, sowie so ziemlich alles, was ihr etwas bedeutet. Es stellen sich die Fragen, ob Maja noch lebt oder nicht, und wo der Verantwortliche f√ºr das Drama steckt. Lea gelangt langsam aber sicher an ihr Limit, w√§hrend Sherlock Wickel sie im Stich zu lassen scheint. 

Konflikt: Es gibt mehrere Konflikte. Eine Psychiatrie sollte Ben Saalfeld heilen, aber verdarb ihn, Aufgrund der Umst√§nde. Rache m√∂chte er an Sherlock Wickel, Markus Wattson und insbesondere Lea nehmen. Hilfe bekommt er dabei von Sarahs Erzfeind Ludwig, beruhend auf Gegenseitigkeit. Ludwig m√∂chte mit Jacks Kette, Sarah und Maja einen moralisch zwiesp√§ltigen Plan umsetzen, um sich selbst von Auswirkungen seiner Schuld zu befreien. Gleichzeitig geht es innerhalb seiner Organisation ebenfalls nicht mit rechten Dingen zu. 

Aufl√∂sung: Am Ende erh√§lt Lea wichtige Erkenntnisse √ºber 's sich selbst Verzeihen. Die Organisation wird √ºberf√ºhrt und die Detektei geschlossen. Es gibt Vers√∂hnungen, Happy Ends und Drama. Maja, Emmas bzw. Jillians Eltern, Ludwig, Liora und Ben werden sterben. Sherlock Wickel und Lea lernen, das Gl√ºck in kleinen Momenten zu sehen. 

Stimmung: Intensiv, d√ºster, humorvoll, spannend, mysteri√∂s, actiongeladen, nah an realen Erfahrungen mit Traumata 

Besonders geeignet f√ºr Menschen, die sich tiefer mit Gef√ºhlen auseinandersetzen m√∂chten. 

Das Drehbuch enth√§lt 125 Seiten, wovon bereits 11 gedreht wurden. Gedreht wird vermutlich wie gewohnt in Plittershagen (Freudenberg, NRW, nahe Siegen) und einem noch unbekannten Drehort als Leas zu Hause. Es sind ggf. Hunde vor Ort, weshalb Tierliebhaber erw√ºnscht sind :)

Ziel des Projekts: Wir m√∂chten mit einer packenden Geschichte die Leute dazu bewegen, dar√ºber nachzudenken, wer sie denn eigentlich wirklich sind. Au√üerdem wollen wir beim Dreh mehr Erfahrung sammeln, uns Qualitativ im Vergleich zu Staffel 1 massivst steigern und die 'Jack'- Timeline meiner Geschichten beenden. 

Wenn alle einverstanden sind, w√ºrde ich nach M√∂glichkeit gerne im Winter mit dem Dreh weitermachen. Diesmal stehe ich auf jeden Fall, im Gegensatz zu bei Mafialiebe, komplett zu Story, Handlung und Co. Ich finde, diese Geschichte bietet einen bestm√∂glichen Abschluss f√ºr die Reihe 'Siegerlandchaos' und ich w√ºrde mich sehr freuen, wenn wir das dann zusammen und in besserer Qualit√§t hinkriegen üòä Da das Drehbuch auch um Einiges k√ºrzer und auf weniger Charakter- Konstellationen beschr√§nkt ist, gehe ich auch von einer schnelleren Umsetzungsm√∂glichkeit als bei Staffel 1: Mafialiebe aus. Drehtage w√ºrden diesmal nach M√∂glichkeit komplett danach ausgerichtet, wer an welchem Tag nach Absprache Zeit hat. 

Ver√∂ffentlicht soll die 2. Staffel mitsamt Bonusepisode ebenfalls auf YouTube werden. 

Gesuchte Rollen:

Ludwig Cifer - Spielalter 40-50 (m/d) - 1 Drehtag - Mafiaboss, intelligent, bedrohlich, ist sehr rassistisch, trans* und behindertenfeindlich, schuldbeladen, gerissen, stirbt am Ende 

Ben Saalfeld - Spielalter 17-18 (m/d) - 1 Drehtag - hasserf√ºllt, rachs√ºchtig, genie√üend, √§ngstlich, spielt Psychospielchen mit seinen Opfern, stark, stirbt am Ende, nachdem er wichtige Erkenntnisse erh√§lt 

Luna Drews - Spielalter 20-30 (w/d) - 1 Drehtag - freundlich, f√ºrsorglich, zuh√∂rend, lebensfroh, ernst, heimlich schwanger, blonde Haare 

Psychologin - Spielalter 20-60 - 1 Drehtag - zuh√∂rend, ernst

Bereits 8 Darsteller*innen sind Teil des Teams.

Zus√§tzlich suchen wir einen neuen Drehort f√ºr Leas und Majas zu Hause. 

Ich suche keine Leute, die sagen: Ja, mach ich mal mit. Ich suche Leute, die sagen: Ja, das w√§re voll cool, dabei zu sein! 

Wenn Interesse besteht, meldet euch gerne bei mir :)
jappycreations@gmail.com 

Zu mir: Ich bin Sarah Marie Sch√§fer, geb. am 01.10.2003 in Siegen, und wohne aktuell in der N√§he von Siegen in einem kleinen Dorf. Nach dem ich meinem verstorbenen Hund Jack versprach, meine Pl√§ne in die Tat umzusetzen und gl√ºcklich zu werden, tat ich dies mit dem Beginn meines ersten Serienprojekts, das abgeschlossen wurde. Fortan spielte ich auch Theater und schloss einige andere Pl√§ne ab. In der Schauspielerei habe ich meinen Weg gefunden und m√∂chte diesen weitergehen. Trotz vieler H√ºrden, wie Autismus, Transidentit√§t und einigen gesundheitlichen Problemen gebe ich nicht so schnell auf und bleibe an meinen Pl√§nen dran.

Anbei sind ein paar Szenen aus Staffel 1 Folge 8 als Vorgeschmack :)

items.text:
üì£üé¨ CASTING CALL - Short Period Drama 

We are casting for The Stuntman, a 3-minute period drama made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 10th November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:
Set in 1920s Wiltshire, The Stuntman follows Ed Morris, a small-town silent cinema owner fighting to keep his theatre alive as the arrival of sound threatens to change film forever. With his fianc√©e Alice by his side, Ed stages one last ambitious stunt in the hope of saving his cinema - and their livelihood. A warm yet bittersweet drama about determination, passion and the march of technological change.

Roles:
Ed Morris (Lead, 28)
Charming, intelligent, and hardworking. Outwardly confident, but hiding a quiet desperation as he struggles to keep silent film alive. Needs strong screen presence and subtle emotional depth.

Alice Fardon (Lead, 22‚Äì23)
Ed‚Äôs fianc√©e. Feisty, loyal, and practical. She supports his dreams but occasionally shows frustration at his all-consuming determination.

Community Extras
Townsfolk gathering to watch Ed‚Äôs big stunt. A mix of ages. Families, workers and individuals. To capture the atmosphere of a 1920s local community.

Apply by: 1st November 2025
To Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to: Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

Please include in email subject: THE STUNTMAN & NAME

items.text:
# CASTING CALL - SHORT SURREAL COMEDY FILM - LONDON AREA 

Looking for someone (early/mid-20s, preferably London-based) to play the lead in a comedy short film about a surreal body swap between a man and a lobster. Think *It's a Wonderful Life* meets *Freak Friday* meets your average straggler/slacker comedy. Much fun to be had!

The role is unpaid, but with food and travel expenses covered. Shooting dates are 5-8th December 2025.

Please take a look at the application pack below:

[https://drive.google.com/file/d/1luS1HP-J9mcAAfXFxPGkIPqI0lEvtdk2/view?usp=sharing](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1luS1HP-J9mcAAfXFxPGkIPqI0lEvtdk2/view?usp=sharing)

To audition, please send your name, age, and your audition tape to madeleineasanderson10@gmail.com.

The deadline for audition tapes is Wednesday 22nd October at

23.59.

We can't wait to see what you send in!

message.text: The Stamford International Film Festival! Only 1hrs train ride from London.   Supported by the British Film Institute‚Äôs BFI NETWORK, the Stamford International Film Festival makes its highly anticipated debut on Saturday, 25th October 2025, set across the iconic George of Stamford (Business Centre) and Stamford School (Ancaster Room & The Great Hall at St. Martin's).Hosted by Green Street Collective, with support from Across The Street Productions and Green Room Place, the festival features a bold, curated programme of international short films - highlighting original voices and underrepresented perspectives from around the world.üé¨ What to ExpectA dynamic line-up of globally sourced short films, handpicked from submissions.Exclusive panels including a BFI NETWORK filmmaker Q&A and 'Stamford: Our Starring Town', see website for list.Inspiring networking opportunities with filmmakers, creatives, and industry guests.A special Awards Ceremony in the Great Hall at Stamford School (St. Martin‚Äôs) - celebrating awards in Drama, Comedy, Director, Actor, Actress, Cinematography, LGBTQIA+, Women in Film & Student Film.   #filmfestival #countryside #indiefilmmaking #supportthearts #EastMidlands #lincolnshire #Stamford

CASTING CALL - PAID MUSIC VIDEO - LOS ANGELES

Project: Music Video Role: ELI (Supporting Lead) Rate: Paid Gig Shoot Date: Monday, October 20 Location: Los Angeles Area 

We are casting the supporting lead role of ELI for a narrative music video. We are looking for an actor who can portray a complex, dramatic arc.

ROLE: ELI

 ‚Ä¢ Gender: Male

 ‚Ä¢ Playing Age: Early 20s (character is a "twenty year old troublemaker" )

 ‚Ä¢ Look: "Scrappy kid with an easy smile" , "grungy but soft". We are looking for someone with a distinct look, similar to the provided reference photos (alt/skater vibe, expressive features).

 ‚Ä¢ Character Arc: This role requires significant emotional range.

 ‚ó¶ Eli begins as a "playful" , charming boyfriend with a "laid-back grin". He and his girlfriend, Bridge, share a "quiet, tender" relationship. However, beneath the surface, he has a "well of self-doubt" that deepens into a "violent, paranoid descent".

 ‚ó¶ The actor must be able to portray this "unraveling" , going from "sweet to scary" as his paranoia and pain warp him into something "unrecognizable-twisted, dangerous, and broken".ÔøΩ

REQUIREMENTS:

 ‚Ä¢ Must have strong dramatic acting ability to portray a "violent, paranoid descent" and "quiet unraveling".

 ‚Ä¢ Must be comfortable with MAKEUP. The role involves styling and makeup (eyeshadow) to create a "demonic" , "decaying" vibe as the character transforms.

 ‚Ä¢ Must be fully available for the shoot date (Monday, Oct. 20) in the Los Angeles area.

TO SUBMIT:

Please send the following to PINKMOOSECASTING@GMAIL.COM with the subject line: "MUSIC VIDEO CASTING - ELI - PLAYIN EXORCIST‚Äù

 1 Headshot and Resume

 2 Demo Reel (if available, please highlight any dramatic roles)

 3 A recent photo (selfie is fine)

 4 Confirmation of your availability for Monday, October 20th

Thank you! We look forward to seeing your submissions.

CU DENVER STUDENT FILM CASTING CALL

Title: *Mannequins*

Genre: Thriller/Horror

Written and Directed by Archer Beck

Produced by Owen Etter

Logline: In a world where otherworldly invaders have forced humanity to live out a sitcom for their entertainment, the daughter figure in a mismatched family of strangers attempts to escape from her lifelong suburban prison.

Synopsis: In a carefully manufactured sitcom world, Daughter begins to see cracks in the illusion of her perfect family life. While she dreams of escaping the endless loop of canned laughter and staged dinners, Father insists they obey their unseen creators and preserve the family‚Äôs image at all costs. Their clash escalates into open rebellion‚Äîuntil Mother, torn between them, helps Daughter break free. Outside the safety of their household, however, Daughter discovers a world ruled by an even stranger, otherworldly power‚Äîand must decide whether freedom is worth the price of losing the only family she‚Äôs ever known.

Main Roles: 

**Daughter **(16-18): Eldest daughter figure who is hellbent on escaping and finding answers.

**Father **(40s): Head of the household who is trying to keep the family unit obedient to the alien conquerors that control them.

**Mother **(40s): Silent caretaker of the family.

**Son **(8-10): Golden child of the household.

Union Status: Non-Union

Production Type: Student Short Film

Runtime: 10-12 minutes

Compensation: Meals Provided, Any Transportation Fees Paid For, Film & IMDb Credit, Copy of Final Cut

Location: Denver Area

Submission Details:

To submit for audition, please send headshot(s), resum√©, and reel (if available) to owen.etter@ucdenver.edu.

# **SANTA WORK AT HERTFORDSHIRE ZOO**
## üéÖ**Be Our Santa at Hertfordshire Zoo!**üéÖ

Hertfordshire Zoo is looking for jolly, enthusiastic, and festive individuals to bring the magic of Christmas to life this year as Santa Claus at **Hertfordshire Zoo in Broxbourne, Hertfordshire.**

You‚Äôll be the star of our popular Christmas event, spreading joy and cheer to families visiting the zoo. From welcoming excited children to listening to Christmas wishes, you‚Äôll create unforgettable memories in our enchanting grotto.

**What We‚Äôre Looking For:**
* A warm, friendly personality with plenty of festive spirit
* Confidence interacting with children and families
* Reliability and professionalism
* Previous performance or grotto experience (preferred but not essential)

**When You‚Äôll Work:**
* 29th & 30th November
* 6th & 7th December
* 13th & 14th December
* 20th, 21st, 22nd, 23rd & 24th December

**PLEASE NOTE** - You are not required to be available to work on all of these dates. Any availability is accepted.

Shifts will be approximately 8 hours per day.

**What We Offer:**
* A fun and rewarding role in a magical setting
* ¬£22.50 per hour
* Full costume and training provided
* The chance to work at one of Hertfordshire's most loved attractions

If you‚Äôve got a hearty ‚ÄúHo Ho Ho!‚Äù and would love to make Christmas unforgettable for our visitors, we‚Äôd love to hear from you.

Apply now by emailing **entertainment@hertfordshirezoo.com**

Hallo alle miteinander,

sind Hier Produzenten unter euch die nach neuen Projekten suchen, dass Sie Finanzieren m√∂chten oder kennt jemanden der dergleichen sucht?

Bitte keine Anfragen wie "ich kann dies und das machen, wenn der Film fertig ist" damit der Film fertig werden kann braucht es einen Sponsor oder einen Produzent/in.

Ja, ich wei√ü welche Interessen ein Sponsor hat, wenn er ein Projekt finanzieren will.

Problem an dem Projekt ist, dass es sich um einen Drama/Psychothriller handelt, und Sponsoren (Gro√üe Firmen, Unternehmen) au√üerhalb der Branche daran kein Interesse haben, weil diese Soziale Projekt unterst√ºtzen).

Das Bild ist eine Requisite f√ºr den Film. Welches Unternehmen will an so einem Film Beteiligt sein in dem so ein Requisit zu sehen ist‚Ä¶

**√úber das Projekt:**

- Titel des Films/Laufzeit: C!N- Ein Drama zwischen Mutter und Tochter / ca. 20min

- Genre:  Drama, Psychothriller

- Kurzbeschreibung: Ein Drama zwischen Mutter und Tochter nimmt einen dramatischen Verlauf und zwingt die Mutter zu einer schwerwiegenden Entscheidung.

Einige grobe Infos als √úberblick (Cast & Crew steht alles):

- 5 Darsteller

- 18 Crewmitglieder

- 1 Location (Dreh findet in einem Objekt statt)

- Drehtage 4-5

Alle Beteiligten unterst√ºtzen das Projekt unentgeltlich.

Die √ºbliche frage die die meisten von euch wohl kennen:

Wof√ºr Sponsor/Produzent, wenn alle unentgeltlich das Projekt unterst√ºtzen?

Diejenigen von euch aus der Branche wissen wieviel Aufwand und Kosten hinter so einem Projekt stecken.

- Unterkunft,

- Verpflegung

- Anreisekosten

- u.v.m.

Wer Interesse hat, mehr Infos ben√∂tigt oder hilfreiche Tipps hat bitte via PN melden.

 

LG
Levent Aksoy

items.text:
Du hast Lust auf kreative Rollen, schnelle Szenen und pointierten Humor?  

Dann k√∂nnte das hier genau dein Ding sein:

Ich starte ein neues Comedy-Projekt auf TikTok, YouTube & Co.  

Geplant sind kurze POV-Sketche, Beziehungsszenen, Alltagssatire und emotionale Mini-Dramen ‚Äì alles mit einem Augenzwinkern und klarer Rollenstruktur.

Drehort ist Berlin.

Was ich suche:

- Schauspielerin im Alter von 28 bis 44 Jahren  

- Spa√ü an geskripteten Szenen und klaren Rollenbildern  

- Offen f√ºr verschiedene Rollen (z. B. Freundin, Kollegin, Date, Aff√§re, Nachbarin etc.)  

- Gef√ºhl f√ºr Timing, Mimik und Punchlines  

- Keine Angst vor Kamera, Humor oder Drama

Was dich erwartet:

- Kreative Zusammenarbeit mit einem Creator, der Storytelling & Timing liebt  

- Szenen mit klarer Struktur, aber Raum f√ºr eigene Ideen  

- M√∂glichkeit, dich als wiederkehrende Figur zu etablieren  

- Hinweis zur Verg√ºtung: Das Projekt befindet sich aktuell in der Aufbauphase und wird zun√§chst ohne feste Bezahlung umgesetzt. Ziel ist es, gemeinsam etwas Starkes aufzubauen ‚Äì mit Credits in jedem Clip und der Option auf langfristige Zusammenarbeit, sobald das Projekt w√§chst.

Interesse?  

Dann schreib mir direkt hier oder per Mail an Dennis.Laubert@Web.de.

Gerne mit kurzem Video, Link zu deinem Profil oder einfach ein paar Zeilen zu dir.

Liebe Gr√º√üe, 

Dennis Laubert

items.text:
RE: SIDE HUSTLE WORK- 

Hey folks! Sorry to post this here, but needing some advice. 

Reaching out here as I have had a bit of trouble finding the typical actor side hustle type work in Los Angeles Ie: event work, catering, brand ambassador work. When I lived in New York, it felt more straight forward finding the companies to apply to with a simple google search, and getting started with work, but it seems a lot of the main ones don't necessarily pop up on google. 

Anyone here that does this type of work, willing to drop the names of a few companies to apply to? 

Coming back to town after some time away and just want to make sure I'm setting myself up financially. 

Lastly - if anyone here works with Runway Waiters and is willing to give a referral, I hear they are great to work for and that'd be amazing! (I do have model agency rep).

Cheers :)

üéÉ **CALLING ALL SCARE ACTORS ‚Äì HALLOWEEN 2025** üéÉ

We‚Äôre looking for **experienced scare actors and stage hands** for an immersive **Private** **Halloween Scare Maze** on **31st October** for a **private high-end client** in London.

This will be a fully-scripted, story-driven experience set inside a building in Mayfair London. 

**We‚Äôre casting the following roles below **üëá

ü™ì **1. THE GROUNDSKEEPER / GRAVE MAN (‚ÄúTHE FETCHER‚Äù)**
*Pre-Show / Entrance Briefing ‚Äì The Landing or Stairwell to Room *
Gruff, cryptic, and slightly unhinged. The living doorman of the dead ‚Äî delivers the guest safety briefing *in character.*
Mud-smeared, lantern in hand, voice low and deliberate. Think grave digger meets storyteller.

.

üïØÔ∏è **3. THE MAID (The Whispering Servant)**
Terrified and loyal ‚Äî the broken servant who knows too much. Swings from whispering calm to pure panic as she reveals the Mistress‚Äôs dark secrets.

üß∏ **4. THE LITTLE GIRL (The Lost Daughter)**
*Room 3 ‚Äì The Children‚Äôs Bedroom*
A silent, unsettling presence. Sweet, innocent, and utterly wrong. Minimal dialogue but maximum impact ‚Äî stillness, presence, and precision are key.

ü©∏ **5. THE MAN IN THE BATH (The Servant / The Butcher)**
*Room 4 ‚Äì The Bathroom*
A guilt-ridden servant trying to protect guests while haunted by his own crimes. Emotional, physical, and unnerving ‚Äî a performance built on tension and breakdown.

üßü‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è **We are also recruiting additional scare actors and stage hands** to support across the maze (movement triggers, jump scares, guest flow, etc).

üìÖ **Date:** 31st October 2025
üìç **Location:** Central London (details upon casting)

Fee: Discussed on Application 

üé≠ **Requirements:**
* Comfortable learning short scripts with a quick turnaround
* Previous acting or immersive performance experience preferred
* Confident with physical performance and guest interaction
* Must be available from 2pm - 2am on the 31st October 2025  

üì© **TO APPLY:**
Email **jay@genzevents.co.uk** with the following:
* Headshot
* Short bio or performance background
* The role(s) you feel best suited for

Please title your email **‚ÄúHalloween Scare Maze Casting" **

items.text: Afruniverse. Setting: Etung

sharedPost.text:
Afruniverse.com/blogs/291/THE-UNLIKELY-HERTTHROB-OF-THE-COCOA-ESTATE : AN AFRUNIVERSE EXPERIENCE

EPISODE 1: THE COCOA PRINCESS
The morning sun poured like honey over Etung, painting the cocoa fields in gold. From a distance, the trees stood proud ‚Äî row after row, lush with pods that whispered legacies of sweat and patience. This was Chief Etim Okon‚Äôs estate, and his only daughter, Obuh, knew every path and scent of it.

She rose early that day, her feet bare against the cool earth, her hair wrapped in a faded scarf that once belonged to her late mother. The workers greeted her as ‚ÄúMadam Cocoa,‚Äù half in jest, half in admiration. Though young, her presence commanded the kind of respect that came from both lineage and labor.

‚ÄúMorning, Madam Obuh,‚Äù Nta the laborer said, balancing his machete.
‚ÄúMorning, Nta,‚Äù she smiled. ‚ÄúMake sure the east block is harvested before noon. Rain‚Äôs coming.‚Äù
‚ÄúYou sabi farm pass some men,‚Äù he teased.
‚ÄúThen tell them to learn,‚Äù she shot back, laughing.

But beneath her laughter, a quiet ache throbbed ‚Äî her father‚Äôs cough had worsened overnight. She walked briskly toward the farmhouse, the sweet smell of cocoa pods giving way to the bitter sting of worry.

THE SHADOW OVER ETIM‚ÄôS HOUSE
Chief Etim Okon lay on a raffia bed, his eyes dim, his breath thin as thread. He was a man carved from the old wood of tradition ‚Äî respected, kind, and generous. But now, death crouched near his door.

‚ÄúObuh,‚Äù he whispered, motioning her closer.
‚ÄúPapa, please don‚Äôt talk. Let me call the nurse from Ikom‚Äî‚Äù
‚ÄúNo. Listen.‚Äù
He clutched her hand, his palm still strong from years in the field.
‚ÄúThey will come for this land. My brothers. They will say you have no right to it. But you are my child ‚Äî my blood, my heir. Promise me you‚Äôll fight for it.‚Äù
‚ÄúPapa‚Ä¶‚Äù
‚ÄúPromise.‚Äù
‚ÄúI promise,‚Äù she sobbed.

The harmattan wind sighed outside as if to carry his last breath. When she blinked, the world went still. The cocoa trees swayed, and her father ‚Äî her pillar ‚Äî was gone.

THE VULTURES GATHER
It didn‚Äôt take long. The following morning, Ojang Okon, her father‚Äôs younger brother, arrived with three men. Their eyes scanned the compound like predators marking prey.

‚ÄúSo, Chief don go,‚Äù Ojang said coldly.
‚ÄúYes, Uncle,‚Äù Obuh replied, standing her ground.
‚ÄúThen you must pack your things. Tradition no allow woman inherit farmland. Cocoa estate belong to the men of the family.‚Äù
‚ÄúThat estate is my father‚Äôs sweat,‚Äù she said, voice trembling.
‚ÄúOur father‚Äôs sweat,‚Äù Ojang corrected. ‚ÄúYou no get say for land matter. You be woman. And woman dey marry out.‚Äù
‚ÄúNot me,‚Äù she whispered.

The men laughed and walked away, leaving the dust of their footsteps in her face. That night, the moon rose like a silent witness as she sat outside, her tears tracing the earth her father once tilled.

THE WHISPERS IN THE DARK
By the third week, rumors had grown like weeds.
‚ÄúShe be illegitimate,‚Äù they said.
‚ÄúShe too stubborn.‚Äù
‚ÄúShe kill her papa with charm.‚Äù

The village drunk swore he saw her sneaking out at midnight. The women at the stream spat her name like sour kola. Only Nta stayed by her side, guarding her gate at night.

Then came the nightmare ‚Äî her father, standing in the field, his hands covered in cocoa dust, his eyes aflame with warning.

‚ÄúThey strangled me, Obuh,‚Äù the ghost said. ‚ÄúAt the hotel in Ikom. But fear not. The truth will rise from the soil. Hold fast. I am with you.‚Äù

She woke drenched in sweat, the sound of drums echoing from the village square. The oracle had spoken ‚Äî the gods had been summoned to expose the killers of Chief Etim Okon.

THE SHOUTS AT THE SHRINE
Under the orange light of dawn, the villagers gathered at the Ikpe shrine. Smoke curled from the priest‚Äôs mouth as he called the spirits. The air thickened; even the birds fell silent.

‚ÄúThe one who killed Chief Etim is among his kin!‚Äù
Murmurs.
‚ÄúThe spirit names ‚Äî Ojang! ‚Äî Ekaette! ‚Äî Ufot!‚Äù

Gasps tore through the crowd. Ojang stumbled backward, eyes wide with fear. The widow, Ekaette, fainted on the spot.

‚ÄúAbomination!‚Äù someone screamed.
‚ÄúThey killed him for land!‚Äù another shouted.

Police sirens pierced the chaos. Inspector Mensah‚Äôs voice barked orders as they dragged the suspects away. But Obuh stood still, her eyes on the sky.

‚ÄúPapa,‚Äù she whispered, ‚Äúthey can bury truth, but they can‚Äôt kill justice.‚Äù

FADE OUT / END OF EPISODE 1
Next on The Unlikely Heartthrob of the Cocoa Estate:
Obuh faces betrayal from within her own compound as a mysterious priest arrives from Calabar with a document that could change everything.

EPISODE 2: THE WHISPERING SHADOWS
The morning after the shrine named names, Etung felt like a bowl of whispers overturned. Doors cracked, eyes peered. Every path carried a rumor. Children were hushed indoors. Women at the stream washed in silence, looking over their shoulders as if the forest could leak secrets.

Obuh tied her mother‚Äôs old scarf tighter and stepped into the compound. The air smelled of wet earth and fermenting cocoa. Nta was already at the gate, machete sheathed, eyes sharp.

‚ÄúDem carry Ojang go station,‚Äù he said softly. ‚ÄúInspector Mensah no dey smile.‚Äù

‚ÄúGood,‚Äù Obuh answered, though her voice cracked. ‚ÄúJustice ‚Ä¶ justice will find its feet.‚Äù

Nta studied her. ‚ÄúMadam Obuh, you no chop. You dey shake.‚Äù

‚ÄúI‚Äôll manage.‚Äù

He hesitated, then offered a calabash of warm corn pap. ‚ÄúSmall food no be sin.‚Äù

She took it with a grateful nod. The pap settled like courage in her belly.

From the footpath, two women passed, glancing in. ‚ÄúSee am‚ÄîCocoa Princess,‚Äù one muttered, half-jeer, half-envy. ‚ÄúDem say she be illegitimate.‚Äù

‚ÄúWhich illegitimate?‚Äù the other snorted. ‚ÄúNa wealth dey cause am.‚Äù

Obuh let the words drift away like smoke. She had learned that day-old gossip always grew new teeth.

By noon, the compound filled with a different energy‚Äîfear dressed as fury. A cluster of village men gathered under the ogbolo tree, voices low, eyes burning.

‚ÄúMob don dey form,‚Äù Nta said, jaw set. ‚ÄúDem wan carry tyre go station. Say make dem burn the killers alive.‚Äù

‚ÄúWhat?‚Äù The calabash almost slipped from her hands.

‚ÄúDem say shrine don talk already, so wetin police dey wait for? But law no be palm wine‚Äîwe no fit drink am anyhow.‚Äù

Her chest tightened. She pictured Ojang‚Äôs face‚Äîdefiant, sly‚Äîand then her father‚Äôs, stained with cocoa dust in her dream. Had Ojang really sunk that low? The thought was bile.

‚ÄúStay here,‚Äù she told Nta. ‚ÄúIf anybody tries to enter, shout. I won‚Äôt be long.‚Äù

She took the narrow path toward the main road, feet skimming the red earth. Around the junction, the mob thickened‚Äîmen with sticks, one with a jerrycan, another with a bundle of old tires. Their chants rose and fell like a curse.

‚ÄúLeave road!‚Äù a voice barked. Inspector Mensah‚Äôs Hilux skidded to a stop in a spray of dust. Two officers jumped down, shotguns slung tight. ‚ÄúAny man wey cross this line go sleep for cell.‚Äù

The crowd growled. A woman, wrapper tied high, cried out, ‚ÄúDem kill Chief Etim like goat! Make fire judge them!‚Äù

Mensah held up a hand. ‚ÄúWe go judge‚Äîbut for court. Anybody wey touch my suspects go enter prison.‚Äù

A tense quiet followed. Slowly, the crowd thinned, like a wave that lost its wind. Tyres‚Äîonce a threat‚Äîrolled uselessly back into a corner. The jerrycan disappeared.

Mensah exhaled, wiped sweat with a handkerchief, and noticed Obuh. ‚ÄúYou shouldn‚Äôt be here.‚Äù

‚ÄúI had to see,‚Äù she said, eyes steady. ‚ÄúAre they safe?‚Äù

‚ÄúFor now. Ojang dey shout say na lie. Ekaette dey cry. The third one‚ÄîUfot‚Äîhe mouth dey shake.‚Äù

‚ÄúGood.‚Äù

Mensah studied her face, something like respect flickering there. ‚ÄúGo home, Miss Etim. Lock your doors tonight. Shadows dey hungry when light don show their face.‚Äù

Evening fell with a quiet threat. Frogs began their choir by the stream. Crickets stitched the dark with needles of sound. In the kitchen, Obuh stirred afang soup, hands moving from long habit, mind far from the fire.

A soft knock came‚Äîthree taps, a pause, two taps. Nta‚Äôs code.

She opened the back door. He slipped in, eyes scanning.

‚ÄúDem trail you?‚Äù she asked.

‚ÄúI no be goat,‚Äù he puffed. ‚ÄúI use another road.‚Äù

‚ÄúWhat is it?‚Äù

‚ÄúRumor say somebody go come drag you out tonight. That Ekaette woman‚Äîher people dey vex. Dem dey swear say shrine lie. Dem want you disgrace.‚Äù

The spoon paused midair.

‚ÄúYou no go sleep main room. Come.‚Äù He led her to the small storage by the back, where sacks of dried cocoa beans sat stacked like sleeping soldiers. ‚ÄúYou go stay here. I go guard front. If alarm ring‚Äîwindow dey lead to banana trees.‚Äù

Obuh wanted to argue, but the tremor in her chest said, Listen. She nodded, grabbed a wrapper and a small cross from the table, and followed.

‚ÄúThank you, Nta,‚Äù she whispered.

He scratched his head. ‚ÄúNa Chief pikin you be. E pain me‚Äîhow dem dey talk anyhow. Me I know wetin I see. Your papa clean. E dey kind.‚Äù

He straightened, as if ashamed of softness. ‚ÄúRest small. I go watch.‚Äù

Night deepened. The estate breathed‚Äîthe rustle of leaves, the occasional thud of a falling pod, the cough of a distant generator in the village.

Obuh lay on a mat, back against the sacks, cross in her palm. Sleep came like a thief and left her with a dream.

Her father again‚Äîstanding by the old storehouse, moonlight whittling him to bone and blessing. His eyes were calmer this time.

‚ÄúWhen ground dey shake, hold root,‚Äù he said. ‚ÄúI left the root where their hand no fit reach.‚Äù

‚ÄúWhere?‚Äù she pleaded. ‚ÄúPapa, where?‚Äù

‚ÄúIn the house of God. In the book. The truth wears a collar. He will come.‚Äù

She reached for him but woke to darkness and a distant sound‚Äîfeet? A whisper? The click of something metallic?

Her heart sprinted. She sat still, clutching the cross. Another sound‚Äîthe back fence rustling.

Then‚Äîa voice from outside, low and ugly: ‚ÄúDrag am out. She dey inside. Fast.‚Äù

Before panic could swallow her, another voice cut the night like a blade. ‚ÄúWho goes there!‚Äù

Nta.

Feet scrambled. A figure darted across the yard, then another. Nta roared and charged; the clang of machete against wood rang like a bell. One intruder thrust back with a stick; Nta ducked, kicked, and the man fell with a pained yelp.

A stone crashed against the kitchen window. Obuh jolted. ‚ÄúJesus!‚Äù

‚ÄúStay!‚Äù Nta yelled, breath ragged. ‚ÄúIf you come out, na wetin dem want!‚Äù

The intruders fled into the trees, curses trailing them. Silence burned. Only Nta‚Äôs heaving breath remained.

Minutes later, he leaned on the doorframe, sweat shimmering on his brow. ‚ÄúDem no get liver pass that. But dem go try again.‚Äù

She stood, legs shaking, and touched his shoulder. ‚ÄúYou saved my life.‚Äù

He shrugged. ‚ÄúNa estate save me too. Chief feed my children with this farm. I no go watch hyena chop the seed.‚Äù

They barred the door with a plank and waited for dawn like it was a person they had sent for.

At first light, Mama Ekaette arrived at the gate with two women and a smear of faux tears.

‚ÄúYou see wetin shrine cause?‚Äù she lamented. ‚ÄúDem embarrass us for whole village. Me wey be wife‚Äînow dem say na me kill am!‚Äù

‚ÄúYou were not his wife,‚Äù Obuh said evenly from the veranda. ‚ÄúYou schemed yourself into his house. And when your charms failed, you brought another woman to widen your net.‚Äù

Ekaette‚Äôs eyes blazed. ‚ÄúMind your tongue, small pikin.‚Äù

‚ÄúThen mind your greed,‚Äù Obuh replied. ‚ÄúYour net will break.‚Äù

Ekaette hissed, then softened her tone, a snake remembering it can sing. ‚ÄúGive the land and end this shame. Tradition no be wet cloth wey you go bend. Your father get brothers. They be men. Cocoa no be for girls. Marry and go.‚Äù

‚ÄúI will go nowhere,‚Äù Obuh said. ‚ÄúThis is my father‚Äôs sweat. If the ground swallows me, it will spit me back on my farm.‚Äù

Ekaette‚Äôs smile curdled. ‚ÄúWe go see.‚Äù

They left, wrappers snapping like flags of war.

By afternoon, Inspector Mensah returned in plain clothes, dust settling on his boots. He sat under the shade of a mango tree where Obuh and Nta had fetched two low stools.

‚ÄúThe attack last night,‚Äù he said. ‚ÄúYou‚Äôre sure you didn‚Äôt see faces?‚Äù

Nta shook his head. ‚ÄúDark like goat belly. But the one wey fall limp‚Äîhe get small limp before he run. Left leg.‚Äù

Mensah scribbled. ‚ÄúGood. We‚Äôll ask around. Some men carry their sins like a limp.‚Äù

He looked at Obuh. ‚ÄúYou‚Äôre not safe, Miss Etim. But neither are they. Ufot is cracking. He asked for water and priest in the night.‚Äù

‚ÄúPriest?‚Äù Her heart stumbled. The dream‚Äôs echo brushed her skin.

Mensah noticed. ‚ÄúSomething?‚Äù

‚ÄúNothing,‚Äù she lied, voice small. ‚ÄúJust ‚Ä¶ grateful.‚Äù

He stood. ‚ÄúWe‚Äôre moving the suspects to Calabar tonight. Less heat there. If anyone threatens you, call. If your uncle comes here, don‚Äôt engage. Lock doors.‚Äù

After he left, Nta whistled. ‚ÄúCalabar! Na there big people dey fall from ladder.‚Äù

‚ÄúShh,‚Äù Obuh muttered, but she was smiling for the first time in days.

Toward evening, word drifted like smoke: Nta has been cleared. The gossip vines cracked with surprise‚ÄîHow come? Wasn‚Äôt he the closest to the Chief? But the police had combed his house, questioned his wife, checked his movements. Nothing. He emerged from the station with weary eyes and a clean slate.

The same could not be said of Ojang. He roared innocence so loudly it sounded like guilt‚Äôs sweat.

Back in the compound, Nta set a small radio on the stool, tuned to lowlife highlife. The cocoa trees hummed in the dusk.

‚ÄúYou dey hear?‚Äù he teased softly. ‚ÄúEven radio know say joy dey near.‚Äù

Obuh laughed, a soft, sun-warmed sound she‚Äôd almost forgotten.

‚ÄúTomorrow,‚Äù she said, eyes on the horizon, ‚ÄúI will go to church.‚Äù

‚ÄúYou wan pray?‚Äù

‚ÄúAnd look for a collar that fits in a dream.‚Äù

Night fell easier this time‚Äîno intruders, no stones. Only crickets and the far-off chant of a prayer group near the old road. Obuh slept without dreams, wrapped in a silence that felt like her mother‚Äôs scarf.

At dawn, she wore a plain dress and walked the red earth road to St. Michael‚Äôs Catholic Church. The building was simple‚Äîwhitewashed walls, a wooden cross, a bell that rang with the stubborn clarity of hope.

After Mass, as worshippers drifted out in clusters of whispers and greetings, a tall priest in his late thirties gathered some hymn books. His face was kind, eyes deep-set, the sort that had seen storms and still believed in umbrellas.

‚ÄúGood morning, Father,‚Äù she said, hesitant. ‚ÄúI am Obuh ‚Ä¶ Etim.‚Äù

He looked up. Something like recognition flickered. ‚ÄúObuh Etim,‚Äù he repeated, voice careful. ‚ÄúI am Rev. Fr. Dominic Asuquo. I have been expecting you.‚Äù

Her breath paused. ‚ÄúExpecting me?‚Äù

He nodded toward the office. ‚ÄúCome.‚Äù

Inside, the room was sparse‚Äîwooden desk, worn Bible, framed photo of ordination day. He opened a drawer, brought out a brown envelope tied with a thin red string, and placed it gently on the table, as one would set down a sleeping child.

‚ÄúThis came to me a month ago,‚Äù he said quietly. ‚ÄúBy hand. Your father came to see me.‚Äù

Her knees weakened; she grabbed the back of the chair.

‚ÄúMy father?‚Äù

‚ÄúYes. He said if anything ever happened to him, I should keep this safe and give it to you. Only you.‚Äù The priest‚Äôs eyes softened. ‚ÄúHe asked me to read its contents, to bear witness.‚Äù

Hands trembling, she untied the string. Inside lay neatly typed pages, a signature she knew better than her own, and a seal.

She looked up, eyes brimming, voice a breath. ‚ÄúIs it ‚Ä¶?‚Äù

Fr. Dominic nodded. ‚ÄúThe Will of Chief Etim Okon.‚Äù

A knock rapped the door‚Äîa hurried, urgent rhythm. The parish catechist peeked in, eyes wide.

‚ÄúFather, sorry. Police from Calabar. They say one suspect collapsed last night. Before he faint ‚Ä¶ he talk say he get confession.‚Äù

Obuh‚Äôs heart hammered.

Fr. Dominic closed the envelope, tapped it twice like a benediction. ‚ÄúGod writes straight with crooked lines,‚Äù he murmured. ‚ÄúChild, today the earth will speak plainly.‚Äù

FADE OUT / END OF EPISODE 2

Next on The Unlikely Heartthrob of the Cocoa Estate:
A confession shakes the village. The will finds its voice. And as a stranger from Ikom steps into the estate with a truckload of cocoa sacks and a smile that hides a story, love brushes past danger for the first time.

EPISODE 3: THE PRIEST‚ÄôS SECRET
The church bell tolled softly through the morning mist, each note hanging like a whispered prayer. Obuh sat rigid before Fr. Dominic‚Äôs desk, the envelope heavy in her trembling hands.

He poured her water. ‚ÄúDrink first,‚Äù he said. ‚ÄúGrief and truth both choke when you hold them too long.‚Äù

She obeyed, the glass clinking lightly against the wood. ‚ÄúFather, I don‚Äôt understand. Why would Papa bring this here? Why not leave it at home?‚Äù

Fr. Dominic folded his hands. ‚ÄúHe feared his brothers. He said they would not rest until they took everything he had. He spoke of...a night of quarrels, about money hidden in cocoa sacks, about jealousy older than forgiveness.‚Äù

Her fingers traced the edge of the paper. ‚ÄúDid he know he was going to die?‚Äù

The priest‚Äôs eyes dimmed. ‚ÄúHe said, ‚ÄòIf they find me dead, tell my daughter to look for light under God‚Äôs roof.‚Äô I thought he meant faith. Now I see he meant this.‚Äù He tapped the will.

Obuh‚Äôs lips parted. ‚ÄúWhat does it say?‚Äù

Fr. Dominic untied the red string again, drew out the first page, and read slowly.

‚ÄòI, Chief Etim Okon of Etung, being of sound mind, hereby declare that all cocoa plantations, warehouses, and savings accounts are to be inherited by my only child, Obuh Etim, and managed in trust until her twenty-fifth year‚Ä¶‚Äô

Tears rolled down her cheeks before she could stop them.

Outside, the parish catechist returned with grim news. ‚ÄúFather, the policeman from Calabar said the suspect, Ufot, did not survive the night. He confessed before dying ‚Äî that Ojang paid him to ‚Ä¶ ‚Äù He hesitated at the sight of Obuh.

Fr. Dominic nodded for him to continue.

‚Äú‚Ä¶ to lure Chief Etim to a hotel in Ikom. Said they meant only to scare him ‚Äî till the rope bit too deep.‚Äù

Obuh gasped, clutching the table. ‚ÄúSo it‚Äôs true. My uncle ‚Ä¶ ‚Äù

The priest rose, placed a steady hand on her shoulder. ‚ÄúVengeance is God‚Äôs, my child. Let justice, not rage, carry your father‚Äôs name.‚Äù

That evening, word spread through Etung like harmattan fire: the Will of Chief Etim Okon exists.
Ojang‚Äôs relatives stormed the church compound demanding it be handed over. Fr. Dominic stood at the gate in his cassock, unmoved.
‚ÄúThis document belongs to the courts,‚Äù he said. ‚ÄúNot to mobs.‚Äù

Behind him, Obuh watched from the window of the mission house, flanked by Nta.
‚ÄúDem no go stop,‚Äù Nta muttered. ‚ÄúGreed no get brake.‚Äù

‚ÄúThen we‚Äôll use the law,‚Äù she replied, voice low but firm. ‚ÄúI‚Äôll go to Calabar myself.‚Äù

Two days later, she arrived at the magistrate‚Äôs office with the priest and Inspector Mensah. The city was loud, unforgiving ‚Äî cars, traders, and dust fighting for space. Mensah led her through corridors smelling of ink and sweat.
‚ÄúBe strong,‚Äù he murmured. ‚ÄúThey will test every word.‚Äù

In court, the will was read. Silence gripped the room. Then Ojang, in chains, burst out laughing.
‚ÄúYou go believe ghost story? Na woman dey deceive una!‚Äù

But when the priest lifted his Bible and repeated, ‚ÄúI was witness to the signing,‚Äù even the magistrate‚Äôs pen paused mid-air.

‚ÄúCase adjourned,‚Äù the clerk announced. ‚ÄúFurther hearing in two weeks.‚Äù

Outside, reporters gathered. ‚ÄúMiss Etim, is it true your father‚Äôs ghost named the killers?‚Äù
She kept walking, chin high. Behind her, Fr. Dominic smiled faintly. ‚ÄúThe truth,‚Äù he said, ‚Äútravels without legs.‚Äù

That night, back at the cocoa estate, Nta brought news. ‚ÄúMadam, stranger don arrive from Ikom. Say he be cocoa buyer. Name Ene Edet.‚Äù

She frowned. ‚ÄúAt this hour?‚Äù

‚ÄúHe say e no like sleep when work still dey.‚Äù

Obuh stepped onto the veranda. A lantern glowed near the gate. There stood a tall man in a neat shirt dusted with travel. He removed his hat, eyes steady but kind.
‚ÄúGood evening, Miss Etim. I‚Äôm Ene Edet. I came to buy beans ‚Ä¶ and maybe find truth, if it‚Äôs for sale.‚Äù

She blinked. ‚ÄúWhat truth?‚Äù

He smiled, just enough to show dimples. ‚ÄúThe kind buried under cocoa leaves.‚Äù

For the first time in months, Obuh felt her heart skip for reasons not born of fear.

FADE OUT / END OF EPISODE 3

Next on The Unlikely Heartthrob of the Cocoa Estate:
As Ene Edet‚Äôs charm draws Obuh closer, his past in Ikom threatens to reveal a secret that could ruin everything. Meanwhile, Ojang‚Äôs allies hatch a desperate plan to reclaim the estate ‚Äî through fire, or through blood.

...to be continued on Afruniverse.com/blogs

items.text:
Du hast Lust auf kreative Rollen, schnelle Szenen und pointierten Humor?  

Dann k√∂nnte das hier genau dein Ding sein:

Ich starte ein neues Comedy-Projekt auf TikTok, YouTube & Co.  

Geplant sind kurze POV-Sketche, Beziehungsszenen, Alltagssatire und emotionale Mini-Dramen ‚Äì alles mit einem Augenzwinkern und klarer Rollenstruktur.

Drehort ist Berlin.

Was ich suche:

- Schauspielerin im Alter von 28 bis 44 Jahren  

- Spa√ü an geskripteten Szenen und klaren Rollenbildern  

- Offen f√ºr verschiedene Rollen (z. B. Freundin, Kollegin, Date, Aff√§re, Nachbarin etc.)  

- Gef√ºhl f√ºr Timing, Mimik und Punchlines  

- Keine Angst vor Kamera, Humor oder Drama

Was dich erwartet:

- Kreative Zusammenarbeit mit einem Creator, der Storytelling & Timing liebt  

- Szenen mit klarer Struktur, aber Raum f√ºr eigene Ideen  

- M√∂glichkeit, dich als wiederkehrende Figur zu etablieren  

- Hinweis zur Verg√ºtung: Das Projekt befindet sich aktuell in der Aufbauphase und wird zun√§chst ohne feste Bezahlung umgesetzt. Ziel ist es, gemeinsam etwas Starkes aufzubauen ‚Äì mit Credits in jedem Clip und der Option auf langfristige Zusammenarbeit, sobald das Projekt w√§chst.

Interesse?  

Dann schreib mir direkt hier oder per Mail an Dennis.Laubert@Web.de.

Gerne mit kurzem Video, Link zu deinem Profil oder einfach ein paar Zeilen zu dir.

Liebe Gr√º√üe, 

Dennis Laubert

I have a B.A. Acting w/ minors in Stage Combat and Voiceover, and have representation. Moved from Chicago this year, have worked commercially and previously been pinned for network shows. üòä 

ChasityCoy.com

Send any audition details/sides to CoyStunts@gmail.com or DM me. üòä

items.text:
Hello All! We are currently seeking 11 people to cast for a project featuring the internet sensation Sturniolo Triplets! We prefer individuals (Male) who have a similar stature to the triplets, around 5'8 ", slim, and 18 years or older, though applicants of any ethnicity are welcome.

The shoot is scheduled for Monday from 11 AM to 4 PM in West Hollywood. Although this gig is unpaid, it offers a valuable opportunity to be featured in a high-profile video, and food will be provided.

If anyone is interested, please let me know. They can contact me at campbellchae@gmail.com. Thank you!

üé¨Genre: Psychological Thriller

Logline: A sleepless student‚Äôs late-night coffee run becomes a haunting journey into his own mind.

üìçLocation: Greater Toronto Area

Shoot Dates: November 14th to November 17th

Union Status: ACTRA / Non-Union.

Food, transportation provided + IMDB Credit. Non-Paid Production. 

Submissions close: October 21st, 2025.

üé≠Roles:

BRIAN - LEAD  Male, early 20s (appears 20-24) Open ethnicity. 

An anxious student constantly overwhelmed by deadlines, expectations, and family pressure. Runs on coffee and adrenaline, but internally he‚Äôs fragile, vulnerable and afraid of failing.

IMANI - SUPPORTING (ACTRA Preferably) Female, late-20s, open ethnicity.

Brian‚Äôs older sister, independent, protective and bluntly honest, but deeply caring. She‚Äôs the only one who dares to confront Brian about his destructive cycle.

GREG - SUPPORTING Male, 40-60s, caucasian (ability to have a Western European accent)

Store employee. Calm, patient, but upsettingly perceptive. His presence feels both ordinary and otherworldly, leaving it unclear if he‚Äôs a real person or a manifestation of Brian‚Äôs mind. He can shift from warm and fatherly to cold and piercing within a minute.

TREY - SUPPORTING (ACTRA Preferably) Male, 20s, black (ability to have a Caribbean, African, or Toronto accent)

Store employee. Alert, sarcastic and slightly comedic relief in an otherwise heavy story. He grounds the store in normalcy, but his presence highlights Brian‚Äôs bizarre reality.

Audition sides: https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1zOvZ9MEK6tVZML1iRnOIA7Zw_J3FdQdd

Submit your audition here: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1lnjQg9KzEXJRy7Kfxy5xZviss-q0NsvscUQCrGMBefg/edit?usp=drivesdk 

Any additional questions to coffeerun.shortfilm@gmail.com

UPDATE: THESE ROLES HAVE BEEN FILLED!

BIRMINGHAM, ALABAMA area
FEATURE FILM
STAND-IN CASTING CALL
-----------------------------
Project: FEATURE FILM - "End The Wait"

Shoot Location: BIRMINGHAM, AL area
--MUST be able to work in the Birmingham, AL area as a LOCAL HIRE!! (Travel/Transportation/Accommodation will not be provided)

DATES NEEDED:  --Monday thru Friday--
MONDAY 10/13/25 -to- THURSDAY 11/13/25
-we do NOT have exact Call/Wrap times, so you should have FULL day/night available to allow for whatever the Call/Wrap Times end up being. **MUST HAVE FULL OPEN AVAILABILITY EVERY DAY Monday - Friday to be able to work every week day as needed

NON-UNION
Rate of PAY:  $175.00 for up to 12 hours (may not work that many hours but you will be paid for the full day even if you get wrapped sooner than 12 hours)  Overtime after 12 hours (if applicable)
_______________________________________________________
ROLES: **STAND-INS**
[CAUCASIAN STAND-IN] Male or Female, Caucasian, age range 20-60, height and weight not as important as long as you have previous Stand-in experience which is REQUIRED. You would be standing in for both our Male and Female Caucasian lead actors

[AFRICAN AMERICAN STAND-IN] Male or Female, African American, age range 20-60, height and weight not as important as long as you have previous Stand-in experience which is REQUIRED. You would be standing in for both our Male and Female African American lead actors
_______________________________________________
TO SUBMIT for these roles: 
Please send us an email ASAP to - onlocationcasting1@gmail.com 
With subject line BIRMINGHAM STAND-IN
Emails must include ALL of the following:   
-First & Last Name
-Phone Number
-Email Address
-Height 
-Weight 
-Clothing and Shoe Sizes 
-Current City/State you are located in
-CONFIRM you are fully available EVERY week day from 10/13 to 11/13 in Birmingham, AL
--Please provide a resume and/or a brief description of your Stand-in experience (project, actor, length of time - please don't just say "Yes I have Standin experience")
-Recent Color Photos of you (prefer cell phone photos rather than professional headshots - NO FILTERS!) . Please include at least (2) photos - (1) Close up and (1) Full Body Standing (make sure you are the ONLY person in your photo, no sunglasses or hats)

DATE NEEDED:  
SATURDAY 10/18/25
-we do NOT have exact Call/Wrap times, so you should have FULL day/night available to allow for whatever the Call/Wrap Times end up being. 

NON-UNION
Rate of PAY:  $150 for up to 8hours (may not work that many hours but you will be paid for the full day even if you get wrapped sooner than 8 hours)  
_______________________________________________________
ROLES: **Featured TALENT**
[COURTROOM PARTICIPANTS] Male and Female, age range 21-70 years old, all ethnicities, wide variety of types, MUST have some type of IMPROV ability or be able to "make up" dialogue on the spot to create certain courtroom situations. You will be presented with different scenarios and expected to create effective and realistic communications and arguments.  Some scenarios will require heightened emotions.
_______________________________________________
TO SUBMIT for these roles: 
Please complete the form at: https://forms.gle/dVmYF8vPFiSUYmUu7
--or-- if you are not able to upload to the google form, send us an email ASAP to - onlocationcasting1@gmail.com 
With subject line COURTROOM Series 10/18
Emails must include ALL of the following:   
-First & Last Name 
-Phone Number
-Email Address
-Height 
-Weight 
-Clothing and Shoe Sizes 
-Current City/State you are located in
-CONFIRM you are fully available on Saturday 10/18 in Atlanta, GA
-Recent Color Photos of you (prefer cell phone photos rather than professional headshots - NO FILTERS!) . Please include at least (2) photos - (1) Close up and (1) Full Body Standing (make sure you are the ONLY person in your photo, no sunglasses or hats)
**Please ALSO include a short self-tape video (can be from your phone) - tell us your first & last name and then act out a short improvised courtroom scenario. (If file is too large to send as an attachment, please send via WeTransfer or Dropbox and NOT as a youtube link!)

items.text:
Hi everyone, quick update to make the group more useful and less noisy üé≠

We‚Äôre introducing **Pre-Approval for Posting** for trusted industry professionals who post opportunities, services, classes and castings. If you‚Äôre an Acting Coach, Theatre, Headshot Photographer, Casting Agency, Agent, Director, Producer or similar, you can apply for pre-approval so your posts skip the approval queue.

If you‚Äôd like to be pre-approved, please fill in this short form: https://forms.gle/6MkgwGQj8sEh6QEj9

Why apply? 

Pre-approved posters have their posts published instantly (no waiting), get a small ‚ÄúApproved Pro‚Äù flair in the group, and help keep the feed relevant for actors.

Who we‚Äôll consider: Acting Coaches, Drama Schools, Theatres, Headshot Photographers (headshot-specific), Casting Agencies, Agents, Directors, Producers, and other verified industry services.

We‚Äôll review each application within 3‚Äì5 business days. 

Please only apply if you‚Äôre legitimately offering industry-related services. Spammy or low-quality promo will be declined.

Any questions, drop them below and we‚Äôll answer. Thanks for helping keep this group professional and useful üôè

ATTENTION, FILMMAKERS! üé¨ Don't miss this opportunity at BBR INDIE FILMS!

‚ÄãWe are honored to feature Dwayne Boyd as our celebrity guest panelist! Dwayne is a CEO, a respected Acting Coach, and the founder of Premier Actors Network (PAN).

‚ÄãMr. Boyd's expertise is invaluable for filmmakers looking to elevate their projects. He's also been seen in major productions like The Hunger Games, Kingdom Business, and Nashville to name a few.

üéØ Filmmakers: Learn his secrets to getting cast, directing actors, and professional packaging. This is your chance to gain a competitive edge!

‚ÄãüéÉ BEST COSTUME WINS A PRIZE!

items.text:
Mickey Mouse Horror Short Film
Hello, I am currently producing a Mickey Mouse Short film, with the working title, The Mouse Killer, which may become the actual title. 

This film is apart of my two existing films, My Horrible Roommate Winnie The Pooh 1 and 2. This serves as the next chapter within the series, that will lead into the 3rd and final My Horrible Roommate Winnie The Pooh film. 

Film Synopsis: two women are out in the woods, hunting down a mythical creature known as, Steamboat Willie, or Willie. 

If it all works out, this short film will be the start of a trilogy of short films. With the final one leading up to My Horrible Roommate Winnie The Pooh 3.

Actors Age Range: 21 to up.

Looking for two females who can play the roles.

Compensation: none

Location: Fort Collins Colorado 

If you're interested, send me a message!

items.text:
Title: Forever Home

Genre: Horror/Thriller

Logline: A young couple tours their dream home with an unsettling real estate agent, only to discover the house holds a dark secret.

Roles:

-Raymond Russo

Age: 45-60

Gender: Male

Ethnicity: White

Description: A veteran real estate agent with a polished exterior. He is charming, articulate, and seemingly trustworthy. Beneath the polished exterior, however, is something deeply unsettling.

Requirements: Actor must be skilled with subtle menace and controlled delivery. Suited look; sharp features a plus.

-Susan

Age: 25-35

Gender: Female

Ethnicity: Any

Description: An optimistic, curious young woman who‚Äôs excited about starting a new chapter with her husband. She‚Äôs practical yet impulsive when her curiosity is piqued.

Requirements: Needs range from natural warmth to terror. Must handle emotional intensity and physical acting in horror scenes.

Production Type: Indie

Contact Information: [luke@lostefilms.com](mailto:luke@lostefilms.com)

Run Time: Short

Compensation: Paid

Union Status: Non-union

Audition Information: Please email headshot, resume and demo reel to email provided (luke@lostefilms.com). We will send a copy of the script and audition instructions.

Shooting Schedule: One short shoot day must happen as soon as possible to capture the brief exterior scenes before leaves are all gone. The other full shoot day will be scheduled close to the exterior shoot day.

Filming Location: Denver metro area

Looking forward to your submissions!
